    <h2>National Cherry Blossom Festival</h2>
    <p>
    RubyNation is being held this year during the time of the 
      <a href="http://www.nationalcherryblossomfestival.org/cms/index.php?id=390">National Cherry Blossom Festival</a>, which takes place between March 27 and April 11.
      This world-famous festival celebrates the 1912 gift of the cherry blossom trees 
      by citizens of Japan to the people of the United States.
      There are lots of events related to the two-week long festival, but the best part is 
      just walking around the tidal basin when the blossoms are in bloom.
      Washington, DC is really beautiful then and worth a visit.
      The festival is planned for the time of year when the blossoms are most likely
      to be in bloom. 
      Check the bloom watch on the festival web site as the time gets closer to get a
      better idea of when the blossoms will be out.
</p>
